        <h1>LeetCode 1846: Maximum Element After Decreasing and Rearranging (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given an integer array arr. You can perform two operations: decrease any element to any positive
                integer, and rearrange elements in any order. The first element must be 1, and the absolute difference
                between any two adjacent elements must be at most 1. Return the maximum possible value of the last
                element.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [2,2,1,2,1]<br>
                Output: 2<br>
                Explanation: Sort to [1,1,2,2,2]. Arranged as [1,1,2,2,2], differences are all at most 1. The maximum
                achievable last element is 2.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int maximumElementAfterDecrementingAndRearranging(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums) {
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        int currMax = 0;
        // Extend the sequence whenever possible.
        for (int val : nums) {
            if (currMax + 1 &lt;= val) {
                currMax++;
            }
        }
        return currMax;
    }
};</code></pre>
